Records already extend [`java.lang.Record`][1]. As Java does not allow multiple inheritance, records cannot extend any other class.

Consider, for example, the following record `Point`:

```java
public record Point(double x, double y) {}
```

You can compile it using:

```java
javac --enable-preview -source 14 Point.java
```

With the help of [`javap`][2], you can can have details about the code generate for `Point`:

```
javap -p Point
```

The output will be:


```java
Compiled from &quot;Point.java&quot;
public final class Point extends java.lang.Record {
  private final double x;
  private final double y;
  public Point(double, double);
  public java.lang.String toString();
  public final int hashCode();
  public final boolean equals(java.lang.Object);
  public double x();
  public double y();
}
```


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/14/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Record.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/14/docs/specs/man/javap.html

